  "history": {
    "en": "Developed in the late 19th and early 20th centuries in the Andalusia region of Spain, particularly in the province of Cádiz. Originated from crosses between Fox Terriers brought by English wine merchants and local ratter dogs used to control vermin in wineries (bodegas). Traditional Spanish working terrier developed for vermin control, hunting, and farm work; recognized by regional and national breed clubs in Spain though not by AKC or FCI",
    "zh": "19世纪末20世纪初在西班牙安达卢西亚地区培育而成，尤其起源于加的斯省。由英国葡萄酒商人带来的狐狸梗与当地用于控制酒窖（酒庄）啮齿动物的捕鼠犬杂交而来。是传统的西班牙工作梗，用于害虫控制、狩猎和农场工作；获西班牙地区和国家犬种俱乐部认可，但未获美国养犬俱乐部或FCI认可。"
  },
